---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Em Kees â€” Lina" bgColor="#F5F5F0">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-14">

    <!-- Header image -->
    <img src="/em-kees/concept-illustration.png" alt="Em Kees" class="w-full mb-10" />

    <!-- Title -->
    <h1 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900" style="font-size: 32px;">Em Kees</h1>

    <!-- Who is Em Kees -->
    <section class="mt-6 mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3" style="font-size: 20px;">Who is Em Kees:</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">
        Em Kees is a folkloric character famous in some Arabic countries, like in Syria, Palestine, Jordan, Lebanon, and Egypt. Usually known to be 'Abo Kees' which is the male version of the character. But for some reason, In Lebanon, Abo Kees is a lady. Em kees stands for 'The Lady with the Bag'. Em kees is a lady that lives in Beirut, and kidnaps kids who are not behaving properly. For example, if the kid doesn't sleep early, do their homework, or even talk back to their parents.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Why Em Kees -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3" style="font-size: 20px;">Why Em Kees:</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">
        The inspiration came after a conversation with some friends, and we all discovered we were all traumatised by this fictional character. However, for our surprise, Em Kees didn't grow old with us. Kids these days don't know who is she.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">
        I then decided to create the story of Em Kees being the lady who is quite old, still living in Beirut. She lost her fame, and became just a normal grumpy old lady. However, she meets a little boy that changes her life.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">
        The story and sketches are still in progress. This part of the story focuses more on the concept art of her house.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Progress -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3" style="font-size: 20px;">Progress:</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">
        The main inspiration for the house design is the traditional Beiruti style, with its three arches.
      </p>
      <img src="/em-kees/1.jpeg" alt="Inspiration" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">
        The house should reflect not just tradition, and the architectural Beiruti style. But also reflect Em Kees's evil personality. This was the first sketch.
      </p>
      <img src="/em-kees/house-sketch-5.jpeg" alt="First sketch" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">
        This the evolution of some concepts that were drawn. The approach to select the final design is based on multiple design reviews with some experts. I decided to break free from logical thinking. The house consists of more exaggerated curves, more pointy corners, to capture the unique spirit of the character.
      </p>
      <img src="/em-kees/house-sketches-evolution.jpg" alt="Sketch evolution" class="w-full mb-6" />
      <img src="/em-kees/concept-illustration5.png" alt="Final concept" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">
        The house in comparison to its surroundings.
      </p>
      <img src="/em-kees/neighborhood.jpeg" alt="Neighborhood" class="w-full mb-6" />
      <img src="/em-kees/street-final.png" alt="Street view" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">
        Some inspiration photos on why the colors, textures, materials were selected.
      </p>
      <img src="/em-kees/8.jpeg" alt="Material inspiration" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">The Past version of the house.</p>
      <img src="/em-kees/old-explain.jpeg" alt="Past version explanation" class="w-full mb-6" />
      <img src="/em-kees/old-version-house.jpeg" alt="Past version of the house" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">The Present version of the house.</p>
      <img src="/em-kees/present-explain.jpeg" alt="Present version explanation" class="w-full mb-6" />
      <img src="/em-kees/present-version.jpeg" alt="Present version of the house" class="w-full mb-6" />

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">Some interior design inspiration.</p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-6">A sketch of how the kitchen might look like.</p>
      <img src="/em-kees/kitchen.jpeg" alt="Kitchen sketch" class="w-full mb-6" />
    </section>

    <!-- Enjoy -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3" style="font-size: 20px;">Enjoy!</h2>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>
